FindMAX
Write a 'C' program to check and print the Maximum number among two numbers without using ternary operator and control statments.

Sample input : int a = 10 , b = 20
Sample Output : MAX = 20
Sample Input
10 20 
Sample Output
MAX = 20

#include<stdio.h>
int main(){
    int a, b;
    scanf("%d", &a);
    scanf("%d", &b);

    a > b && printf("MAX = %d", a);
    b > a && printf("MAX = %d", b);
    b == a && printf("Both are same");
}


