FindEvenOdd
Write a 'C' program to check and print that given number is even or odd without using ternary operator and control statments.

Sample input : int a = 10
Sample Output : EVEN

Sample input : int a = 125
Sample Output : ODD
Sample Input
10
Sample Output
Even


#include<stdio.h>
int main(){
    int a;
    scanf("%d", &a);

    a%2 == 0 && printf("Even" );
    a%2 == 1 && printf("Odd");
}


